A 'Sympetrum costiferum' is a species of dragonfly belonging to the family Libellulidae.
It is commonly known as the Saffron-faced meadowhawk or Saffron-winged meadowhawk.
This dragonfly is small to medium-sized, measuring approximately 3.5 cm in length.
It has bright orange wings with black veins, a brown thorax, and a yellowish-brown abdomen.
The wings are transparent near the base and become more opaque towards the tip.
Males have a reddish-orange face while females tend to have a yellowish-gray face.
They are found in a variety of habitats including ponds, lakes, streams, and wetlands throughout North and Central America.
